Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.74,0:10:35.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一场美丽的转变开始了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A beautiful transformation begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.51,0:10:38.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}被烟熏黑的贫瘠冰山\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The barren, sooty iceberg
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.28,0:10:41.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}变幻出灼热的光晕\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}now sports a glowing halo...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.79,0:10:44.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有彗尾\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.00,0:10:54.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些粉尘层描述着大约40亿年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These layers tell the story of how the comet was made,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.13,0:10:56.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}彗星产生的过程\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some four billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.97,0:11:04.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在4万代人的历史中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}During the 40,000 generations of humanity,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.68,0:11:07.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}至少有大约10万次\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there must have been roughly 100,000 apparitions
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.28,0:11:09.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}耀眼的彗星划过天际\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of a bright comet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.05,0:11:10.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那个时候\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For all that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.95,0:11:15.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们只能仰望  不禁的惊叹\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the best we could do was look up in helpless wonder,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.79,0:11:18.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}无助的人们不知所措\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}prisoners of Earth with nowhere to turn
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.29,0:11:21.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}除了恐惧和悔恨 没有更好的办法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for an explanation beyond our guilt and our fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.06,0:11:26.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}后来 两个人的友情为人类的思想\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But then a friendship began between two men that led
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.30,0:11:29.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}带来了翻天覆地的革命\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to a permanent revolution in human thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.14,0:11:34.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}艾萨克・牛顿和爱德蒙・哈雷 也是始料未及\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Isaac Newton and Edmond Halley could not know it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.21,0:11:37.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们的研究成果将我们从\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but their collaboration would ultimately set us free
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.98,0:11:41.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这颗小星球的局限中彻底解放\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from our long confinement on this tiny world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.08,0:11:50.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1664年的这颗彗星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Comet of 1664
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.88,0:11:54.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}令整个欧洲恐惧颤栗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sent shivers of dread throughout Europe,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.48,0:11:57.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}随后发生的大瘟疫和伦敦大火灾\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the terror seemed justified when the Plague
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.05,0:12:00.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恰巧印证了人们的恐惧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the Great Fire of London followed soon after.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.62,0:12:05.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那血色的长发\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There, with long bloody hair,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.09,0:12:08.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}耀眼的星辰威胁整个世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a blazing star threatens the world
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.39,0:12:13.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}带来饥荒  瘟疫 战争\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with famine, plague and war.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.73,0:12:17.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}王子们的死亡\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To princes, it spells death...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.57,0:12:21.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}王国多了无数的墓碑\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to kingdoms, many crosses...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.64,0:12:25.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不可避免的财产损失\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to all estates, inevitable losses...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.95,0:12:28.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}腐烂的牧群\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to herdsmen, rot,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.98,0:12:31.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}颗粒无收的庄稼汉\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to plowmen, hapless seasons,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.85,0:12:36.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}海上的风暴\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to sailors, it brings storms,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.46,0:12:40.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}暴动的市民\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to cities, civil treasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.50,0:12:49.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但有一个孩子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But for one child,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.87,0:12:52.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并不觉得彗星有那么恐怖\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the comet was not the least bit frightening.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.38,0:13:01.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对他来说 只是惊奇\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For him, it was a thing of wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.81,0:13:04.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和我们一样  爱德蒙・哈雷生性好奇\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like all of us, Edmond Halley was born curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.88,0:13:06.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哇塞\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hell's bells!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.02,0:13:11.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他很幸运  他的父亲支持并鼓励他的求知欲\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He was lucky to have a father who encouraged and nurtured his curiosity,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.86,0:13:14.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}给他买了最好的科学仪器\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}buying him the best scientific instruments
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.89,0:13:16.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}资助他的探险考察\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and even funding his expedition
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.83,0:13:19.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为了画出第一张精确的南半球星空图\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to make the first accurate star map of the Southern Hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.87,0:13:22.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哈雷20岁时从牛津辍学\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Halley dropped out of Oxford when he was 20,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.74,0:13:24.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}去了圣赫勒拿岛\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and sailed to St. Helena,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.70,0:13:28.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一个位于赤道以南  非洲的西海岸的小岛\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an island below the equator, off the west coast of Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.55,0:13:35.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哇塞\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hell's bells.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.35,0:13:37.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}问题是 没人告诉哈雷\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The problem was, nobody told Halley
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.48,0:13:40.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}岛上的天气状况是如此糟糕\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the weather on St. Helena was generally lousy;
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.35,0:13:43.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他用了12个月\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it took him 12 frustrating months
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.36,0:13:48.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}才观测到足够的南半球星星来绘制完整的星图\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to observe enough southern stars to make a complete map.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.36,0:13:52.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}古希腊的众神和英雄人物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The gods and heroes of ancient Greece were now joined
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.40,0:13:55.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由虚构的图形将他们汇聚在一起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the mythic figures of a new world and age,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.54,0:13:59.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}巨喙鸟  指南针  天堂鸟\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a toucan, a compass, a bird of paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.58,0:14:11.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当哈雷带着《南天星表》回到家时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When Halley came home with the other half of the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.62,0:14:13.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他的星空图造成了轰动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}his map created a sensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.59,0:14:18.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}商人和探险家可以根据随处可见的星星导航\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now merchants and explorers could navigate by the stars visible anywhere on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.52,0:14:21.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当时 伦敦的皇家学会\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the time, the World Society of London
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.59,0:14:23.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是世界上科学发现的集散地\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was the world's clearinghouse of scientific discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.80,0:14:26.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的格言是 不人云亦云\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its motto, "Nullius in verba,"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.57,0:14:29.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}总结出了科学方法的中心思想\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sums up the heart of the scientific method.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.30,0:14:32.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它是拉丁语中的 亲自求证\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's Latin for "see for yourself."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.30,0:14:35.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}换言之 质疑权威\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In other words, "question authority."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.97,0:14:39.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哈雷的星图引起了学会实验室负责人的注意\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Halley's star maps caught the attention of the Society's Curator of Experiments.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.95,0:14:41.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我也想让你看看他的样子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'd show him to you if I could,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.71,0:14:44.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但罗伯特・胡克并没有留下任何的肖像画\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but no portrait of Robert Hooke exists from his time,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.78,0:14:47.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有他的事迹口耳相传\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}only the verbal descriptions of his contemporaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.79,0:14:51.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们说他 瘦弱 驼背 丑陋\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They called him "lean, bent, ugly."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.09,0:14:54.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他可能是最有创造性的天才\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He was possibly the most inventive person who ever lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.23,0:14:55.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不论他的外表如何\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And despite his appearance,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.99,0:14:59.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他在当时的伦敦炙手可热\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he was the most sought-after party guest in all of London.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.13,0:15:00.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为何\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.90,0:15:03.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为胡克永不满足的求知欲\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hooke's insatiable curiosity
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.40,0:15:05.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}覆盖了所有的领域\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}encompassed absolutely everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.57,0:15:10.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}胡克发现了一个小宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hooke discovered a little cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.44,0:15:13.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们至今沿用他给它的命名  细胞\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we still call it by the name he gave it, the cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.44,0:15:13.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}单词原意：单人房
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.81,0:15:15.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}胡可通过观察一片软木片发现了细胞\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hooke discovered the cell by looking
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.61,0:15:18.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}正是用了他自己的一项发明\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at a piece of cork with one of his own inventions,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.35,0:15:20.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}复合显微镜\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the compound microscope.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.82,0:15:24.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他提出的观点比达尔文的进化论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He anticipated aspects of Darwin's theory of evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.16,0:15:27.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}早了几乎200年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by almost 200 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.26,0:15:29.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}胡克又改良t望远镜\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hooke also improved the telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.36,0:15:31.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他根据观察天体所做的素描\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The drawings he made of the astronomical bodies he observed
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.00,0:15:34.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}见证了他异乎寻常的准确性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}attest to his uncanny precision.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.13,0:15:38.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1666年的伦敦大火灾摧毁了伦敦中部\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After the Great Fire destroyed central London in 1666,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.64,0:15:41.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}胡克与建筑师 克里斯多佛・雷恩合作\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hooke partnered with the architect Christopher Wren
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.44,0:15:44.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}重新设计 建设 伦敦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to redesign and rebuild the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.51,0:15:48.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}胡克是当时首屈一指的实验主义者\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hooke was the foremost experimentalist of his age.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.45,0:15:49.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}使用弹簧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Using coiled springs,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.82,0:15:51.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他提出了 弹性定律\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he derived the "law of elasticity,"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.55,0:15:54.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们称之为  胡克定律\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}known today as Hooke's Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.05,0:15:56.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他改良了气泵\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He perfected the air pump,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.52,0:15:58.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}达到了当时的技术顶峰\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the height of technology in its time,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.89,0:16:02.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并将之用于声音和呼吸实验\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and used it to experiment on respiration and sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.66,0:16:05.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他用大麻做实验\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And he experimented with cannabis.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.70,0:16:08.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他在一次皇家学会的会议上报告\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He reported to a meeting of the Royal Society
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.37,0:16:11.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}据他的一位船长朋友说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that a sea captain friend of his
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.04,0:16:13.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}「经常食用这个东西\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"had so often experimented with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.64,0:16:15.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不会令人产生恐惧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that there is no cause of fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.24,0:16:18.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只会带来喜悦」\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}though possibly there may be of laughter."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.38,0:16:25.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}咖啡在17世纪的英格兰\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But coffee was the drug of choice for England
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.05,0:16:26.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是最受欢迎的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the 17th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.55,0:16:29.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}咖啡馆遍布伦敦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Coffeehouses sprang up all over London.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.37,0:16:44.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人们在那里获取新闻\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is where people came to get news,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.44,0:16:48.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}发表新的观点 讨论时事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to launch new ventures, and to debate ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.17,0:16:50.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}咖啡馆是这个注重阶级的社会中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The coffeehouse was an oasis of equality
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.58,0:16:53.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}平等的绿洲\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a class-obsessed society.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.25,0:16:55.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这里  穷人不需要给富人让座\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here, a poor man needn't give up his seat
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.91,0:16:58.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也不用屈从他的观点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to a rich man, nor submit to his opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.72,0:17:01.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像是民主制度的实验室\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was a kind of laboratory of democracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.55,0:17:04.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这种高度兴奋刺激的气氛中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In this highly caffeinated atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.22,0:17:08.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哈雷和胡克 与克里斯多佛・雷恩讨论着一个谜团\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Halley and Hooke met Christopher Wren to discuss a deep mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.96,0:17:12.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为何行星如此运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why do the planets move as they do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.40,0:17:14.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天文学家约翰内斯・开普勒在此前的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The astronomer Johannes Kepler had demonstrated,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.93,0:17:16.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}80多年 就证明了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some 80 years before,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.43,0:17:19.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}行星绕太阳公转的轨道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the orbits of the planets around the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.04,0:17:22.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并不是正圆  而是椭圆形\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were not perfect circles, but actually ellipses,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.44,0:17:25.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}行星越靠近太阳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that the closer a planet was to the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.74,0:17:28.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}运动的越快\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the faster it moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.71,0:17:30.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为什么\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.98,0:17:35.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}会是太阳发出某些看不见的力量 导致这种变化吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Could some invisible force from the Sun be responsible for this change in motion?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.19,0:17:36.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果是  又是如何导致的呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If so, how did it work?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.92,0:17:40.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以用一个简单的数学定律描述吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Could there be a simple mathematical law to describe it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.33,0:17:44.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像胡克的弹性定律那样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe something like Hooke's Law of Elasticity?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.67,0:17:49.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有可能\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.47,0:17:51.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是 尝试之后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But try as he might,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.10,0:17:52.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}克里斯多佛・雷恩没有答案\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Christopher Wren couldn't figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.24,0:17:54.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}总好过没有尝试过\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Damned if I haven't tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.77,0:17:56.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我的能力有限\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's beyond me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.28,0:17:58.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我押上这本价值40先令的书\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'll wager a book worth 40 shillings
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.28,0:17:59.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}谁能解决 谁就拿去\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the man who can solve it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.81,0:18:01.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我拿定了  雷恩先生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That book is mine, Mr. Wren.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.95,0:18:03.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我已经完成了计算\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I've already done the calculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.32,0:18:04.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哈雷非常开心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Halley was delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.65,0:18:06.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}快让我们见识见识  胡克先生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Show us, Mr. Hooke.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.49,0:18:10.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但几个月过去  胡克也没能做到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But months passed, and Hooke failed to deliver.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.09,0:18:11.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他算不过来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He couldn't do the math.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.76,0:18:13.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没人能够\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}None of them could.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.59,0:18:15.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最后 哈雷厌烦了胡克的借口\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Finally, Halley had enough of Hooke's excuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.93,0:18:18.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哈雷知道 肯定在某个地方 有某个人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Halley knew there must be someone, somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.00,0:18:21.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以做到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}up to the challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.31,0:18:30.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}剑桥大学的数学家怎么样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What about that mathematician at Cambridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.31,0:18:32.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}聪明的家伙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Clever fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.14,0:18:34.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他多年前就解决了光线本质的核心问题\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He had solved central questions about the nature of light
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.51,0:18:38.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他当时只有22岁\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}years before, when he was still only 22.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.35,0:18:40.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他发明了反射望远镜\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And he invented the reflecting telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.32,0:18:41.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}怪人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Odd bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.02,0:18:44.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}销声匿迹过一段时间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dropped out of sight a while back;
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.19,0:18:47.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对胡克本人和他的光学理论有些不同看法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some squabble over Hooke and his discovery about light.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.33,0:18:48.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}走了极端  无法自拔\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Went completely to pieces over it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.89,0:18:51.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从此在剑桥大学隐居\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and has been hiding out in Cambridge ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.46,0:18:54.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哈雷很期待 这个怪人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Halley wondered if this strange, and by all accounts,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.50,0:18:57.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}据说 很难相处的人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}exceedingly difficult man, might succeed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.14,0:18:58.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是否能成功\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where Hooke and others had failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.74,0:19:00.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他当时并不知道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What he couldn't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.31,0:19:03.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有任何人会想到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what no one could possibly imagine at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.31,0:19:04.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}整个世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were the countless ways
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.84,0:19:08.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就在1684年8月的某一天\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the world would be forever changed by this meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.15,0:19:10.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}各个方面都因为这次见面 从此改变\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on an August day in 1684.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.02,0:19:21.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}艾萨克・牛顿出生于英格兰\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Isaac Newton was born in England
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.65,0:19:23.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1642年的圣诞节\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on Christmas Day in 1642.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.86,0:19:29.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}父亲在他出生前就过世了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Before he even opened his eyes, his father was already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.83,0:19:34.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}3岁时 母亲也抛弃了他\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}His mother left him when he was only three
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.77,0:19:37.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直到11岁才再次见面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and did not return until he was 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.87,0:19:41.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她已经有了新的家庭\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When she did, it was with a new family and husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.67,0:19:44.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿鄙视他的继父\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a stepfather who Isaac Newton despised.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.48,0:19:52.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}悲惨家庭环境中的唯一避风港\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Newton's refuge from his miserable family life
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.72,0:19:56.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是牛顿对于科学研究的热情\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was his passion to understand how things worked,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.56,0:19:59.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}特别是自然科学\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}especially nature itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.76,0:20:05.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1661年  天资聪颖的艾萨克进了剑桥大学三一学院\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1661, the talented young Isaac entered Trinity College at Cambridge University
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.50,0:20:08.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他在学校很不合群\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where he was a consistently lousy student,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.17,0:20:10.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有家人和朋友\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one without friends or a loving family
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.00,0:20:13.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}给他丝毫的温暖和鼓励\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to provide any warmth or encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.57,0:20:17.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿不与人交流  把自己关在房间里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Newton mostly kept to himself, sequestered in his room,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.24,0:20:19.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}学习古希腊的哲学\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}studying ancient Greek philosophers,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.75,0:20:22.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几何和语言\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}geometry and languages,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.05,0:20:23.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}琢磨着更深层次的问题\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and pondering deep questions
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.82,0:20:28.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}关于自然  空间  时间  运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the nature of matter, space, time, and motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.82,0:20:33.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这位才华初露的科学家也是一名狂热的神秘主义者\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This budding scientist was also a passionate mystic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.53,0:20:35.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿相信这种只为小部分\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Newton believed that a secret knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.23,0:20:37.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}古代哲学家所知的炼金术\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}called alchemy, known only to a small group of ancient philosophers,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.56,0:20:41.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}正等着他去重新发现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was waiting to be rediscovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.60,0:20:45.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他希望可以学会把普通金属\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He hoped to learn how to change ordinary metals
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.27,0:20:46.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}变成金银的方法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into silver and gold,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.91,0:20:49.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或许可以做出生命合剂\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and maybe even cook up the elixir of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.78,0:20:51.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以此长生不老\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the key to to immortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.91,0:20:55.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他一心想从圣经的字里行间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He was also obsessed
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.85,0:20:59.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}找到隐藏的信息\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with finding hidden messages in the words of the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.09,0:21:03.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他梳理了不用语言的译本\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He combed through translations in several different languages,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.42,0:21:06.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}试图破译加密了的上帝的指示\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hoping to decipher coded instructions from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.90,0:21:15.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他做了详尽的计算\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He made elaborate calculations in an effort
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.13,0:21:19.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只为发现基督再次降临的日期\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to discover the date of the Second Coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.54,0:21:21.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}穷其一生研究炼金术\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}His lifelong research in alchemy
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.44,0:21:24.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}研究圣经  可惜没有任何突破\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and biblical chronology never led anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.25,0:21:32.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当哈雷找到牛顿的那天\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When Halley found Newton that fateful day,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.12,0:21:36.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿一直过着隐居的生活\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he was living as a virtual recluse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.06,0:21:41.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿自从罗伯特・胡克公开指责他\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Newton had gone into hiding 13 years earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.00,0:21:46.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}剽窃胡克关于光学和颜色的突破性成果\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}after Robert Hooke had publicly accused Newton of stealing
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.67,0:21:48.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}已经隐居了13年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}his groundbreaking work on light and color.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.90,0:21:51.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}事实上 牛顿才是那个\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact, it was Isaac Newton
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.94,0:21:53.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}解开光谱谜团的人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who solved the mystery of the spectrum of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.81,0:21:56.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并不是罗伯特・胡克\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not Robert Hooke.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.61,0:21:58.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这对他的打击很大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This wound was painful and deep,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.78,0:22:01.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿下定决心从此再不让自己陷入\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and Newton resolved to never expose himself to that kind
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.58,0:22:03.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那种被人羞辱的境地\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of public humiliation ever again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.25,0:22:06.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}先生 你可能不记得了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sir, I don't suppose you recall
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.29,0:22:08.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们几年前见过\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our meeting a few years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.32,0:22:10.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我记得 哈雷先生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yes, Mr. Halley.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.29,0:22:11.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}抱歉来打搅你\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'm sorry to bother you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.82,0:22:14.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不用客套 有话直说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Never mind the formalities, get to your point.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.69,0:22:17.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我一直与我们的朋友  胡克和雷恩在讨论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I've been talking with our friends, Mr. Wren and Mr. Hooke.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.96,0:22:20.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}胡克那个人渣不是我的朋友\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That scoundrel Hooke's no friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.97,0:22:22.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我明白\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yes, I understand, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.77,0:22:24.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}重点是 我们一直在讨论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the thing is we've been debating
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.80,0:22:27.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}行星运动的难题\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the puzzling question of planetary motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.71,0:22:29.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们都认同 某种吸引的力量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We all agree that some force of attraction
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.61,0:22:32.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}来自太阳  控制着行星的运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the Sun governs the motions of the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.31,0:22:35.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们感觉一定能有一条数学定律\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We suspect there must be a mathematical law
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.28,0:22:36.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}来形容这种\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to describe how this force
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.95,0:22:39.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}根据距离而改变的力量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}changes with distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.45,0:22:40.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以您的能力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And knowing of your skill...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.79,0:22:42.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没错 重力所产生的吸引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yes, yes, the attraction of gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.12,0:22:44.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与距离的平方成反比\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}weakens with the square of the distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.36,0:22:46.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是椭圆轨道的原因\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's why the planets move in ellipses.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.96,0:22:49.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但您是怎么知道的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But, sir, how can you know this?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.56,0:22:52.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}怎么了 我5年多前就算出来了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why, I have calculated it some five years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.50,0:22:55.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}求你了 让我见识一下\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I beg you, show it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.40,0:22:56.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}计算的结果在这里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The calculation is here...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.80,0:22:58.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就在周围\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.81,0:23:00.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没关系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, no matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.04,0:23:01.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我重新做一份\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I shall redo it and be sure
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.51,0:23:02.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然后寄给你\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to send it on to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.58,0:23:04.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太不可思议了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is stupendous!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.04,0:23:06.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}相见恨晚啊\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why have we not had word of it before?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.35,0:23:08.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿还记得上次\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Newton remembered all too well
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.18,0:23:11.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他提出新的理论时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what Hooke had done to him
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.22,0:23:13.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}胡克的所作所为\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the last time he put forth an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.89,0:23:15.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就在哈雷开始怀疑\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just when Halley may have begun to wonder
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.99,0:23:19.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿是否也像胡克那样吹牛时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if Newton was bluffing as Hooke had done earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.16,0:23:23.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}信使带来牛顿的一封信\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a messenger arrived with an envelope from Newton.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.90,0:23:29.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是现代科学理论的开篇\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here are the opening pages of modern science
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.70,0:23:32.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}包含了对于大自然的洞察\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with its all-embracing vision of nature...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.01,0:23:36.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}运动定律  万有引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}universal laws of motion, gravity...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.78,0:23:38.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不单适用于地球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not just for the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.41,0:23:41.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也适用于整个宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but for the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.38,0:23:44.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哈雷迫不及待地回到剑桥\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Halley raced back to Cambridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.68,0:23:47.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿大人  我求你赶紧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mr. Newton, I beseech you to work all of this
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.75,0:23:50.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}把这些都写进你的书里吧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into a book as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.36,0:23:53.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我向你保证 皇家学一定会出版你的书\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I can assure you the Royal Society will publish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.86,0:23:55.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但还有一个小问题\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there was one little problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.73,0:23:58.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们同意\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We are in agreement
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.20,0:24:01.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿先生的成果是伟大的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that Mr. Newton has produced a masterpiece.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.37,0:24:05.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是  皇家学会恐怕\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, I'm afraid the Royal Society has...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.04,0:24:08.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为《鱼类历史》的惨淡销售\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}well, regrettably sales for the History of Fish...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.98,0:24:12.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}造成我们的财政状况并不乐观\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have not lived up to our financial expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.91,0:24:15.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是一本很棒的书\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's an impressive book.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.75,0:24:17.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}包罗万象\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Extremely comprehensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.65,0:24:19.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}真的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Really.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.45,0:24:22.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}使用了大量的插图来描述\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's filled with lavish illustrations of...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.99,0:24:26.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}鱼类\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}well, fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.46,0:24:28.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}销量惨淡带来更大的问题\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The disappointing sales led to a bigger problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.90,0:24:31.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是皇家学会在出版《鱼类历史》上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Royal Society pretty much blew
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.43,0:24:34.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几乎花了整年的预算\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its total annual budget on the History of Fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.43,0:24:37.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们现金短缺\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact, they were so strapped for cash,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.17,0:24:39.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们不得不用那卖不掉的书\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they had to pay poor Halley's salary
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.61,0:24:42.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}来抵本应支付给哈雷的工资\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with copies of their worst-selling book.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.31,0:24:45.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有钱来印刷牛顿的《原理》\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With no money to print Newton's Principia,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.51,0:24:48.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}科学革命 命悬一线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the scientific revolution hung in the balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.91,0:24:55.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}要不是哈雷的努力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Without Halley's heroic efforts,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.89,0:24:57.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿的这部巨著\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the reclusive Newton's masterwork
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.04,0:25:00.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可能永无出头之日\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}might never have seen the light of day.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.40,0:25:02.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哈雷的坚持不懈\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Halley was a man on a mission,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.60,0:25:06.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将牛顿的天才展现给了全世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}absolutely determined to bring Newton's genius to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.21,0:25:08.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那个科学革命以前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That pre-scientific world,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.78,0:25:11.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}靠恐惧来统治的世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the world ruled by fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.25,0:25:14.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}已经被推向了革命的边缘\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was poised at the edge of a revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.38,0:25:17.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一切就看爱德蒙・哈雷能否\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Everything depended on whether or not Edmond Halley
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.75,0:25:20.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将牛顿的新书推向世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could get Newton's book out to the wider world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.76,0:25:23.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哈雷编辑并且出版了牛顿的书\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Halley resolved not only to edit Newton's book,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.56,0:25:26.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}全都自掏腰包\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but to publish it at his own expense.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.56,0:25:28.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在牛顿完成的头两卷里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Newton completed the first two volumes,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.46,0:25:30.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}用数学公式\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}laying the mathematical framework
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.67,0:25:33.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}来描述物理运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for the physics of motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.24,0:25:36.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}第三卷彻底决定了谁才是咖啡馆的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The third volume would settle once and for all
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.27,0:25:38.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}赌局赢家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who won the coffeehouse wager.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.14,0:25:40.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿运用他的原理可以解释\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Newton applied his principles to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.41,0:25:42.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球上所有的运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all the known motions of the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.54,0:25:44.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}月亮和其它行星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Moon and the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.91,0:25:47.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不幸的是 还有一个问题\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unfortunately, there was this problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.92,0:25:49.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哈雷又变成了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now Halley also took on the role
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.75,0:25:52.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿的心理医生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of Newton's psychotherapist.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.69,0:25:56.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}艾萨克  那个  胡克先生要求\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Isaac, I'm afraid that Mr. Hooke requires
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.06,0:25:59.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在你的第三卷序言里向他致谢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an acknowledgment in the preface of your third volume.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.39,0:26:00.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我已经做过了啊\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But I have done so.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.73,0:26:02.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}谢谢他 雷恩先生还有你\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thanking him, Mr. Wren and yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.86,0:26:05.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}激励我重新思考有关天文学的事情\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for prodding me to think again on astronomical matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.97,0:26:09.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}胡克在伦敦到处说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mr. Hooke has been going about London saying
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.20,0:26:11.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你的万有引力定律是借鉴了他\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that you got the Law of Gravity from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.71,0:26:13.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我要告他这个小...\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why, that litigious little...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.31,0:26:14.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}做梦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.64,0:26:16.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我宁可烧了我的第三卷\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I would sooner burn the third volume
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.48,0:26:18.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也不会让这种谎言玷污它\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than deface it with such a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.48,0:26:19.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让胡克去死吧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To hell with Hooke.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.95,0:26:21.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他会被人们遗忘\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He will be long forgotten
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.28,0:26:23.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而你的理论会被人们永远歌颂\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when your ideas are still being celebrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.45,0:26:29.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}又是这些恶心的书\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}More copies of that dreadful book?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.56,0:26:32.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}家里都快放不下了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Wherever shall we put them all?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.29,0:26:33.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我和你说过的 玛丽 亲爱的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We talked about this, Mary, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.83,0:26:36.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是科学院给我的薪水\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is my salary from the Society.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.50,0:26:39.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们也拿不出其它东西了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They have nothing else with which to pay me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.30,0:26:43.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果胡克和牛顿也能像你这样就好了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If only Mr. Hooke and Mr. Newton were more like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.60,0:26:45.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哈雷和雷恩决定和胡克对质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Halley and Wren decided to confront Hooke
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.61,0:26:47.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}关于他不实的言论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about his false claims.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.27,0:26:49.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是我的定律 我告诉你\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That law is mine, I tell you!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.91,0:26:51.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我先证明的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I proved it first.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.28,0:26:53.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那就把你的证据拿出来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then fetch your proof here at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.11,0:26:54.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让我们看看\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Let us see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.35,0:26:57.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}反正我们都等了这么久了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Surely we have waited on it long enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.95,0:27:01.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你只要相信我的话就可以了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You'll simply have to take my word for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.09,0:27:03.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}空口无凭或许在其它地方行得通\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Empty claims may persuade elsewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.49,0:27:05.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但这里不行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.49,0:27:05.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}"勿轻信人言"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.69,0:27:08.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}拿不出来就闭嘴  胡克先生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Put up or shut up, Mr. Hooke.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.20,0:27:12.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿这个混蛋  我要他付出代价\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Blasted Newton. I'll make him pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.50,0:27:25.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}"自然哲学的数学原理"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.35,0:27:30.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果没有爱德蒙・哈雷\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If it wasn't for Edmond Halley,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.82,0:27:32.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿绝没有机会构思\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Newton's great book would've never been conceived,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.99,0:27:35.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}书写 出版他的书\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}nor written, nor printed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.52,0:27:37.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}好吧  那又怎样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Okay. So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.83,0:27:39.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对我们来说有什么不一样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What difference does that make to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.99,0:27:42.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有什么大不了的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What's the big deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.04,0:27:52.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当牛顿在这栋房子里诞生时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When Isaac Newton was born in this house
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.21,0:27:54.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1642年  那是的世界和现在完全不一样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in 1642, the world was very different.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.88,0:27:57.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个人看到天空中的众多星星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Everyone looked at the perfection
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.11,0:27:59.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}像钟表一样极有规律的准确运行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the clockwork motions of the planets in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.78,0:28:01.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只能想到的是出自\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and could only understand it as the work
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.72,0:28:03.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一个伟大的「钟表匠」\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of a master clock maker.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.38,0:28:05.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还能怎么解释\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How else to explain it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.49,0:28:07.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们只能想出一种解释\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There was only one way such a thing could come about
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.86,0:28:09.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以他们的想象力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in their imagination;
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.32,0:28:11.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有一种答案\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}only one answer for them--
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.36,0:28:12.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上帝\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}God.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.83,0:28:15.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}出于我们还不了解的原因\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For reasons beyond our understanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.13,0:28:17.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上帝就是这么创造的太阳系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}God just created the solar system that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.70,0:28:20.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个解释却是一个死结\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But this explanation is the closing of a door.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.67,0:28:24.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并无法解释其它的问题\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It doesn't lead to other questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.35,0:28:35.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿来了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Along came Newton,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.68,0:28:38.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上帝宠爱的人  大天才\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a God-loving man who's also a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.82,0:28:40.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他能用完美的数学语句\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He could write the laws of nature
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.99,0:28:43.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}写出大自然的定律\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in perfect mathematical sentences--
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.42,0:28:45.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对宇宙有效的方程式\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}formulas that applied universally
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.89,0:28:48.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对苹果 月亮 行星都有效\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to apples, moons, planets
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.86,0:28:51.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有很多\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so much more.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.07,0:28:55.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}虽然仍身处中世纪\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With one foot still in the Middle Ages,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.94,0:28:59.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿已经想象出了整个太阳系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Isaac Newton imagined the whole solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.21,0:29:01.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿的万有引力和运动定律\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Newton's laws of gravity and motion
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.58,0:29:05.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}揭示了太阳如何维系这些遥远的星球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}revealed how the Sun held distant worlds captive.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.45,0:29:07.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他的定律使人们不再需要\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}His laws swept away the need
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.61,0:29:09.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}用「钟表匠」来解释\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for a master clock maker
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.25,0:29:12.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为什么太阳系能如此精准的运行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to explain the precision and beauty of the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.72,0:29:15.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}万有引力就是钟表匠\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gravity is the clock maker.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.96,0:29:19.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}事物遵循我们发现的戒律运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Matter obeyed commandments we could discover,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.36,0:29:21.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}遵循圣经没有提到过的定律运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}laws the Bible hadn't mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.96,0:29:24.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿的理论解释了为什么太阳子会是这样的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Newton's answer to why the solar system is the way it is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.97,0:29:28.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也为其它无数的问题打开了大门\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}opened the way to an infinite number of questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.54,0:29:30.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}《原理》的内容里包括\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Principia also happened to include
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.57,0:29:32.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}微积分的发明\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the invention of calculus,
